Detect Sentiment in Unstructured Text

Process unstructured data during model creation and categorize sentiment as positive, negative, or neutral.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.
In Model Setup, select a variable that contains unstructured data, such as comments, and click Sentiment Analysis from the Transform dropdown menu.
Click Update Model. Return to Model Setup after the update is complete.
You can adjust bucket names by clicking Edit Buckets then the pencil to update the name.
Uncheck bucketed sentiments and use the dropdown menu to exclude sentiments from the model or store them into an “Other” category.
title: Analyzing Sentiment in Unstructured Text with Salesforce
